1
00:00:00,210 --> 00:00:01,940
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:02,010 --> 00:00:03,440
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:05,140 --> 00:00:06,810
(Episode 21)

4
00:00:09,610 --> 00:00:10,620
Jeong Han.

5
00:00:11,580 --> 00:00:12,650
Did you see the video?

6
00:00:13,850 --> 00:00:15,190
You...

7
00:00:15,920 --> 00:00:18,660
- You set all this up, didn't you?
- What?

8
00:00:18,760 --> 00:00:21,090
Posting that video
of your wife falling...

9
00:00:22,230 --> 00:00:23,830
and getting my Ju Ah disciplined...

10
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:25,830
That was you?

11
00:00:27,230 --> 00:00:28,230
Jeong Han.

12
00:00:29,470 --> 00:00:34,040
- How could you do this?
- Let me explain what happened.

13
00:00:34,370 --> 00:00:35,440
Outside. Now!

14
00:00:41,050 --> 00:00:43,050
(Onjeong Market
Merchants' Association)

15
00:00:44,480 --> 00:00:47,520
Look... Let me explain, Jeong Han.

16
00:00:47,850 --> 00:00:49,150
I'll explain everything.

17
00:00:51,060 --> 00:00:55,060
Fine. Let's hear it.
Why the heck did you do it?

18
00:00:55,590 --> 00:00:58,060
What the heck were you thinking,
pulling a stunt like that?

19
00:00:58,230 --> 00:01:00,600
That was... I was just...

20
00:01:00,670 --> 00:01:03,800
It was so you could get on
"Human Theater," wasn't it?

21
00:01:04,340 --> 00:01:05,340
What?

22
00:01:05,970 --> 00:01:08,710
My gosh.
Seong Mi was right about everything.

23
00:01:09,710 --> 00:01:12,480
You made me feel guilty
and played on my sympathy...

24
00:01:13,040 --> 00:01:15,410
to get everything you wanted,
didn't you?

25
00:01:15,510 --> 00:01:17,080
No, Jeong Han.

26
00:01:17,080 --> 00:01:20,550
Come on.
How could you use your own wife?

27
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:24,990
I seriously had no idea
you were such a piece of trash.

28
00:01:25,590 --> 00:01:27,730
You're right. I'm a piece of trash.

29
00:01:28,690 --> 00:01:30,200
I did something I never should have.

30
00:01:30,760 --> 00:01:32,460
How much of this was a setup?

31
00:01:33,230 --> 00:01:34,400
Your wife...

32
00:01:34,700 --> 00:01:37,340
Is that why she deliberately went
to Ju Ah's office to "help" her?

33
00:01:37,840 --> 00:01:38,970
And after all that?

34
00:01:39,570 --> 00:01:41,470
You said you weren't expecting
anything in return?

35
00:01:42,140 --> 00:01:43,680
You two-faced...

36
00:01:43,940 --> 00:01:46,640
I've done something unforgivable.

37
00:01:47,210 --> 00:01:48,550
I really messed up.

38
00:01:50,050 --> 00:01:51,420
And we had no idea.

39
00:01:52,050 --> 00:01:54,550
We were so grateful,
we even invited you to our home.

40
00:01:55,750 --> 00:01:56,750
Man.

41
00:01:57,090 --> 00:01:58,620
You must've gotten a kick out of it.

42
00:01:59,190 --> 00:02:01,130
We must have looked like
a bunch of fools to you.

43
00:02:01,790 --> 00:02:04,360
Fools? No, absolutely not.

44
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:06,460
You should've just blackmailed me,

45
00:02:06,460 --> 00:02:09,400
saying your wife was injured
because of the ball I hit.

46
00:02:10,240 --> 00:02:14,970
You should've just told me to do
"Human Theater" because I hurt her.

47
00:02:16,040 --> 00:02:19,480
If you had,
I wouldn't feel this betrayed.

48
00:02:20,280 --> 00:02:21,310
How could you...

49
00:02:21,910 --> 00:02:26,180
How could you deceive me
and my family like this?

50
00:02:27,050 --> 00:02:29,520
Deceive you?
No, I was going to tell you.

51
00:02:29,590 --> 00:02:31,960
I tried to tell you and apologize
so many times.

52
00:02:32,220 --> 00:02:34,930
No. You didn't say a word.

53
00:02:35,390 --> 00:02:37,100
If you hadn't gotten caught,

54
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:39,000
you would've hidden it forever.

55
00:02:39,060 --> 00:02:41,770
No. I really was going to tell you.

56
00:02:41,770 --> 00:02:42,830
You were?

57
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:46,940
Your daughter, Ju Ah,
said we should bury it.

58
00:02:48,610 --> 00:02:49,710
Ju Ah knows?

59
00:02:50,380 --> 00:02:51,380
Yes.

60
00:02:52,710 --> 00:02:53,750
So that's why...

61
00:02:54,350 --> 00:02:56,950
you were asking
if Ju Ah had said anything to me?

62
00:02:57,620 --> 00:02:58,680
Yes.

63
00:02:59,850 --> 00:03:01,020
You son of a...

64
00:03:01,820 --> 00:03:02,920
You really are...

65
00:03:03,860 --> 00:03:05,520
You're not even human!

66
00:03:19,300 --> 00:03:21,570
Does this mean you forgive me?

67
00:03:22,570 --> 00:03:23,580
Yes.

68
00:03:27,910 --> 00:03:31,050
Stop smiling and eat.
You said you were craving this.

69
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:37,820
But what made you decide to come
to my place and cook for me?

70
00:03:38,090 --> 00:03:40,730
- That wasn't all.
- There's more?

71
00:03:41,430 --> 00:03:45,660
I also made a list of cool spots
and great restaurants for our dates.

72
00:03:45,860 --> 00:03:47,630
You lived abroad
for a long time, babe,

73
00:03:47,630 --> 00:03:49,230
so there must be a lot of places
you haven't seen here.

74
00:03:50,600 --> 00:03:52,540
- What?
- What?

75
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:54,310
What did you just call me?

76
00:03:55,110 --> 00:03:56,870
What did I call you?

77
00:03:57,740 --> 00:03:58,740
"Babe."

78
00:04:01,350 --> 00:04:04,480
That's what couples
call each other, you know.

79
00:04:04,780 --> 00:04:06,850
Calling each other
"Bin" and "Princess" all the time...

80
00:04:06,850 --> 00:04:08,390
is a little cheesy.

81
00:04:09,390 --> 00:04:10,520
"Babe." I like it.

82
00:04:10,990 --> 00:04:12,720
I'll start calling you "babe"
from now on, too.

83
00:04:13,290 --> 00:04:14,290
Babe.

84
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:16,960
Just hurry up and eat.

85
00:04:20,530 --> 00:04:24,400
I'll do my best to make sure
this never happens again.

86
00:04:24,970 --> 00:04:26,270
Don't make promises you can't keep.

87
00:04:26,770 --> 00:04:29,640
I sounded out my mom yesterday,
pretending it was about a friend.

88
00:04:29,710 --> 00:04:31,880
She said she sees many patients
with issues...

89
00:04:31,880 --> 00:04:33,240
with their mothers-in-law.

90
00:04:34,110 --> 00:04:37,350
Already thinking about in-law drama?
That actually makes me really happy.

91
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:40,690
I can't say anything around you,
can I?

92
00:04:42,420 --> 00:04:44,520
Anyway, my grandma and my mom...

93
00:04:45,120 --> 00:04:48,290
- They're against it.
- But you still want to be with me?

94
00:04:48,390 --> 00:04:51,300
Yes. No matter what anyone says,

95
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:53,700
I don't give up on what I want.

96
00:04:56,370 --> 00:04:58,040
I'm not eating this.

97
00:04:58,370 --> 00:04:59,370
Why not?

98
00:04:59,640 --> 00:05:03,510
- I'm too happy to eat.
- My gosh.

99
00:05:05,180 --> 00:05:08,250
- Come on, just eat.
- All right. I should eat, too.

100
00:05:18,420 --> 00:05:20,430
Your seat belt.

101
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:43,480
Yes, Dad?

102
00:05:43,720 --> 00:05:46,850
Hyun Bin, what am I going to do?
Jeong Han found out.

103
00:05:47,150 --> 00:05:50,490
I sent him the video by mistake,
and now he knows everything.

104
00:05:52,220 --> 00:05:56,030
You were going to tell him anyway.
Just give him a sincere apology.

105
00:05:56,390 --> 00:06:00,200
I did. I apologized,
but he won't forgive me.

106
00:06:00,730 --> 00:06:02,130
What can you do?

107
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:05,470
This is on you, Dad.
You have to accept it.

108
00:06:09,140 --> 00:06:10,680
Now that my dad knows,

109
00:06:10,740 --> 00:06:13,310
it's only a matter of time
before the rest of my family does.

110
00:06:16,610 --> 00:06:20,380
I'll go and ask your family
for forgiveness, babe.

111
00:06:21,320 --> 00:06:24,760
No, I'll deal with my family,

112
00:06:24,820 --> 00:06:27,590
so you deal with yours. Got it?

113
00:06:31,830 --> 00:06:33,600
It looks like acid reflux.

114
00:06:34,470 --> 00:06:37,030
Stomach acid is flowing back up,
giving you constant heartburn...

115
00:06:37,200 --> 00:06:39,140
and making you feel like
something's stuck in your throat.

116
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:43,140
It's because I have a habit
of lying down right after I eat.

117
00:06:43,410 --> 00:06:46,210
Yes, exactly. If you don't change
your eating habits,

118
00:06:46,280 --> 00:06:49,810
- taking medicine won't help at all.
- Oh, dear.

119
00:06:50,350 --> 00:06:54,850
My goodness, Doctor.
Are you mad at me or something?

120
00:06:55,090 --> 00:06:56,920
You're scaring me. Goodness...

121
00:06:57,320 --> 00:06:59,960
No, I just...
I'm not trying to scare you.

122
00:07:00,290 --> 00:07:03,860
That's a bad habit,
so you're going to get a lecture.

123
00:07:04,860 --> 00:07:08,170
Now, make sure you finish your meals
at least three hours before bed,

124
00:07:08,300 --> 00:07:11,440
and cut out alcohol and coffee, too.
All right?

125
00:07:11,940 --> 00:07:14,910
- Yes, Doctor.
- Right. You can go now.

126
00:07:14,970 --> 00:07:17,380
- This way, please.
- Go on. Yes, go ahead.

127
00:07:20,850 --> 00:07:21,950
Hey, what's wrong?

128
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:23,480
Are you not feeling well?

129
00:07:24,320 --> 00:07:27,720
No, I'm just a little tired.

130
00:07:31,790 --> 00:07:33,990
Tell him to take it
with his medicine.

131
00:07:34,530 --> 00:07:36,430
Did he seem really out of it?

132
00:07:36,590 --> 00:07:39,300
Not really.
He just seems a bit drained.

133
00:07:39,830 --> 00:07:42,570
Do you think it's because of
that business with Dong Ik?

134
00:07:43,170 --> 00:07:44,170
I've got to go.

135
00:07:44,540 --> 00:07:45,540
Wait, Dae Han.

136
00:07:45,970 --> 00:07:46,970
What is it, Mom?

137
00:07:47,410 --> 00:07:50,880
By any chance,
do you have a girlfriend?

138
00:07:51,640 --> 00:07:53,980
- What?
- Am I wrong? Am I right?

139
00:07:54,780 --> 00:07:56,250
Well...

140
00:07:56,980 --> 00:07:58,020
So...

141
00:07:58,380 --> 00:08:01,550
Is that why you refused
to go on that blind date?

142
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:03,820
It hasn't been that long
since my divorce,

143
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:05,390
so I thought maybe it's too soon.

144
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:08,730
- Don't be silly.
- Right?

145
00:08:11,230 --> 00:08:14,400
This is wonderful.
Good to see you smiling again.

146
00:08:15,730 --> 00:08:18,370
So what's she like?
Is she a good person?

147
00:08:18,970 --> 00:08:22,070
You're worried I'll fall
for the wrong kind of person again,

148
00:08:22,470 --> 00:08:23,740
aren't you?

149
00:08:23,980 --> 00:08:27,510
None of that was your fault.
Don't even think that.

150
00:08:28,010 --> 00:08:29,050
Mom, the thing is...

151
00:08:29,180 --> 00:08:33,220
Well, she has a child.

152
00:08:36,190 --> 00:08:38,920
And does that bother you?

153
00:08:39,090 --> 00:08:41,360
No. I'm happy about it.

154
00:08:42,130 --> 00:08:44,460
- As long as you're happy.
- Right?

155
00:08:48,130 --> 00:08:50,270
I've never seen this look
on your face before, son.

156
00:08:51,770 --> 00:08:53,910
I think I really like her.

157
00:08:55,210 --> 00:08:57,040
Now, I'm dying to meet her.

158
00:08:58,080 --> 00:09:00,210
Mom, just give me
a little more time.

159
00:09:00,610 --> 00:09:01,610
I'll get going.

160
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:17,760
She'll answer, right?
I'm sure she will.

161
00:09:29,570 --> 00:09:32,080
Dae Han? What's up?

162
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:33,440
Hey, Dong Suk.

163
00:09:33,910 --> 00:09:36,750
I was just calling to see
if you had plans tonight.

164
00:09:37,680 --> 00:09:38,680
Why?

165
00:09:39,150 --> 00:09:42,020
What do you mean, why?
I just wanted to see you.

166
00:09:42,550 --> 00:09:44,860
I'm busy today.
With the store acquisition,

167
00:09:44,920 --> 00:09:46,320
I have to go to training
at the head office.

168
00:09:46,860 --> 00:09:48,760
Okay. Then,

169
00:09:49,490 --> 00:09:50,760
what about this weekend?

170
00:09:51,060 --> 00:09:55,270
This weekend, I'm supposed to tour
the top stores with my supervisor.

171
00:09:55,730 --> 00:09:57,200
I see.

172
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:00,910
Hey... Are you trying to avoid me?

173
00:10:02,140 --> 00:10:03,270
I'm free tomorrow.

174
00:10:03,670 --> 00:10:04,740
What?

175
00:10:05,140 --> 00:10:08,180
I'm free for lunch tomorrow.

176
00:10:09,050 --> 00:10:10,280
In that case,

177
00:10:10,820 --> 00:10:13,180
do you want to have lunch
with me tomorrow?

178
00:10:14,150 --> 00:10:15,820
Yes, okay.

179
00:10:16,020 --> 00:10:19,790
Really? Great, I'll see you then.
Okay, bye.

180
00:10:21,030 --> 00:10:25,330
Yes! Nice!

181
00:10:26,130 --> 00:10:27,300
What are you doing?

182
00:10:28,070 --> 00:10:30,630
It's physical therapy.
I'm stretching my sore shoulder.

183
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:32,040
Nice!

184
00:10:32,140 --> 00:10:34,710
Oh, man... Yes!

185
00:10:38,910 --> 00:10:40,980
- Eun Bin.
- Yes?

186
00:10:41,050 --> 00:10:43,550
Hey, is this the right answer
for question 40?

187
00:10:47,850 --> 00:10:49,390
The fill-in-the-blank question?

188
00:10:52,590 --> 00:10:56,160
"There is a natural..."

189
00:10:56,660 --> 00:10:59,960
"assumption of truth or..."

190
00:11:00,430 --> 00:11:03,830
- What's this? "Bias?"
- Never mind if you don't know.

191
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:06,040
What? Who says I don't know?
You, little...

192
00:11:06,740 --> 00:11:09,410
Min Ji Hu,
go get me a glass of water.

193
00:11:09,610 --> 00:11:11,780
Why? So you can check the answer key
while I'm gone?

194
00:11:12,610 --> 00:11:15,210
No! Hey, what do you take me for?

195
00:11:15,710 --> 00:11:16,850
Hold on!

196
00:11:17,110 --> 00:11:18,920
I haven't moved a muscle.

197
00:11:23,020 --> 00:11:27,390
What? "Cognitive misers?"

198
00:11:28,230 --> 00:11:29,560
Hey, what does this mean?

199
00:11:30,800 --> 00:11:32,160
A cognitive miser.

200
00:11:33,060 --> 00:11:35,700
- And what does that mean?
- Are you asking me?

201
00:11:35,770 --> 00:11:38,540
I was just checking if you knew,
you brat!

202
00:11:39,270 --> 00:11:40,370
Looks like you know your stuff.

203
00:11:40,670 --> 00:11:41,770
Studying's going well, right?

204
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:46,340
How could it be?
Mom, she doesn't know anything.

205
00:11:46,440 --> 00:11:49,310
Hey! I'm helping with your tutoring,
so zip it!

206
00:11:49,380 --> 00:11:51,320
Did I ask for it? You offered.

207
00:11:51,580 --> 00:11:55,390
Just be patient a little longer.
I'm finding you a good tutor, okay?

208
00:11:55,590 --> 00:11:58,090
Auntie,
just take your time finding one.

209
00:11:58,090 --> 00:12:03,030
And keep telling Grandpa and Dad
that I'm tutoring Ji Hu. Got it?

210
00:12:03,090 --> 00:12:04,530
Goodness. Will do.

211
00:12:04,860 --> 00:12:06,260
I'm off to my training
at the head office.

212
00:12:06,330 --> 00:12:09,770
Are you sure?
You're not meeting your boyfriend?

213
00:12:09,830 --> 00:12:13,470
Hey! Not in front of Ji Hu!
Since when do I have a boyfriend?

214
00:12:14,170 --> 00:12:16,110
Gosh, I'm going to be late.
I'm heading out.

215
00:12:18,210 --> 00:12:21,980
Hey, don't you think your mom's got
a boyfriend these days?

216
00:12:22,450 --> 00:12:25,050
Eun Bin, I have a question for you.

217
00:12:25,150 --> 00:12:27,550
Gosh, what now?
What problem is it this time?

218
00:12:28,090 --> 00:12:30,490
There's no chance at all
between you and Woo Jae, right?

219
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:33,860
Hey, what makes you think
there's no chance?

220
00:12:33,990 --> 00:12:35,860
Have you ever thought about
just giving up?

221
00:12:36,330 --> 00:12:37,830
Absolutely not.

222
00:12:39,660 --> 00:12:43,200
- This is going to get messy.
- What are you talking about?

223
00:12:46,100 --> 00:12:47,910
(Taehan)

224
00:12:47,970 --> 00:12:50,840
(Hwangbo Hye Su, Vice President,
Strategic Planning Division)

225
00:12:57,520 --> 00:12:58,520
Yes?

226
00:12:58,520 --> 00:13:00,350
(Taehan Group)

227
00:13:02,350 --> 00:13:04,990
The design team meeting
isn't for a little while.

228
00:13:05,060 --> 00:13:06,860
I have something to report
before then.

229
00:13:07,460 --> 00:13:10,530
What is it?
Is Director Baek scheming again?

230
00:13:10,830 --> 00:13:13,230
It's regarding
Director Yang Hyun Bin.

231
00:13:16,800 --> 00:13:18,000
We have an emergency.

232
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:19,500
An emergency?

233
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:23,240
- Pacu Nacho got a job offer.
- What?

234
00:13:25,780 --> 00:13:29,080
- Seriously? From which brand?
- Cartio.

235
00:13:29,180 --> 00:13:31,620
Cartio? Wow.

236
00:13:31,620 --> 00:13:34,220
Isn't that
the super hot Spanish brand?

237
00:13:34,220 --> 00:13:35,550
Exactly.

238
00:13:37,720 --> 00:13:40,790
What if Pacu Nacho ditches us
and just leaves?

239
00:13:40,990 --> 00:13:42,290
No way.

240
00:13:42,360 --> 00:13:45,260
But he's not on good terms
with Ms. Gong, so he might leave.

241
00:13:52,370 --> 00:13:54,510
These are the mock-ups
from the hair and makeup team,

242
00:13:54,610 --> 00:13:56,170
but they're not finalized yet.

243
00:13:56,510 --> 00:13:59,810
We'd love to get your opinions too,
Vice President and Director.

244
00:14:00,510 --> 00:14:02,080
What do I know?

245
00:14:02,950 --> 00:14:04,150
What does Pacu Nacho think?

246
00:14:04,850 --> 00:14:07,380
I think they're all good.

247
00:14:08,420 --> 00:14:10,450
Please pick one anyway, Director.

248
00:14:13,920 --> 00:14:16,360
What's this? Did they make up?

249
00:14:16,930 --> 00:14:19,860
Right?
They're all sweet again today.

250
00:14:20,130 --> 00:14:22,600
I guess it was just
a little lovers' quarrel.

251
00:14:23,570 --> 00:14:25,200
I was worried for nothing.

252
00:14:28,610 --> 00:14:32,380
You like Option A.
It's more vibrant, isn't it?

253
00:14:34,880 --> 00:14:37,450
The photo shoot is this weekend.
Are you coming to the set?

254
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:40,580
Of course.
Dr. Han is going to be there.

255
00:14:40,990 --> 00:14:44,790
- I'll tell Mr. Park not to come.
- Why?

256
00:14:45,560 --> 00:14:48,090
Because I hate seeing Dr. Han
being nice to Mr. Park.

257
00:14:49,290 --> 00:14:52,000
You can't just ban the main designer
from the set.

258
00:14:52,100 --> 00:14:55,300
Yes. I'll give him another job to do
and send him far away.

259
00:14:55,430 --> 00:14:56,870
Come on.

260
00:14:58,700 --> 00:14:59,900
Hold on a second.

261
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:01,840
Hi, Dad.

262
00:15:04,780 --> 00:15:06,380
Okay, I will.

263
00:15:09,280 --> 00:15:10,280
What did he say?

264
00:15:10,750 --> 00:15:12,680
He wants to see me after work.

265
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:14,450
It must be about that thing.

266
00:15:14,990 --> 00:15:18,020
- I'm going with you.
- No, I told you I'd handle it.

267
00:15:18,520 --> 00:15:22,130
- Then I'll give you a ride.
- You're tired. Don't bother.

268
00:15:22,330 --> 00:15:25,800
I'm not tired. It's a good excuse
to see your face a little longer.

269
00:15:27,030 --> 00:15:29,870
In that case, after you drop me off,
go visit your parents.

270
00:15:30,130 --> 00:15:34,200
Go check on your father, okay?
I'm sure he's going through a lot.

271
00:15:35,010 --> 00:15:38,440
No. After what he did,
he deserves to be miserable.

272
00:15:50,050 --> 00:15:52,460
- What is it?
- Please talk to me, Jeong Han.

273
00:15:52,660 --> 00:15:54,060
I have nothing to say to you.

274
00:15:54,390 --> 00:15:56,260
- Jeong Han, please.
- Let go of me!

275
00:15:57,290 --> 00:15:58,830
I couldn't tell you because
I cherished our friendship.

276
00:15:59,530 --> 00:16:02,570
I was enjoying being friends again,
just like old times.

277
00:16:02,630 --> 00:16:06,740
Right. I'm sure you had fun.
You must've loved making me a fool.

278
00:16:06,940 --> 00:16:09,540
- How can you say that?
- I'm warning you.

279
00:16:09,910 --> 00:16:13,110
Don't you ever think about
setting foot in my clinic again.

280
00:16:14,410 --> 00:16:16,910
- Jeong Han.
- Don't talk to me. Just get lost.

281
00:16:17,850 --> 00:16:19,380
You're not even human.

282
00:16:32,930 --> 00:16:34,700
Dad, are you okay?

283
00:16:34,870 --> 00:16:38,170
You should've told me this happened!
Why didn't you tell me?

284
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:42,870
Are you scolding me right now?

285
00:16:43,410 --> 00:16:44,480
For goodness' sake.

286
00:16:44,940 --> 00:16:47,950
You must've been stressed out alone.
That's why I feel so bad.

287
00:16:48,650 --> 00:16:50,910
You didn't know, so there's
no reason for you to feel bad.

288
00:16:54,990 --> 00:16:57,760
Ju Ah, why did you want to bury it?

289
00:16:57,920 --> 00:17:01,790
- I knew you'd react this way.
- You still should have told me.

290
00:17:01,860 --> 00:17:03,590
Please, stop being so angry!

291
00:17:04,060 --> 00:17:05,060
I just...

292
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:07,560
I'm sorry. I really am.

293
00:17:07,800 --> 00:17:09,370
Stop apologizing.

294
00:17:09,730 --> 00:17:12,600
I should've just done the show
from the beginning, you know?

295
00:17:12,770 --> 00:17:16,740
I was being stubborn for no reason,
and you suffered at work for it.

296
00:17:17,110 --> 00:17:19,740
But it all worked out in the end,
didn't it?

297
00:17:19,840 --> 00:17:24,250
Wait. That whole family set this up.
They were all in on it, right?

298
00:17:24,310 --> 00:17:26,850
I bet Yang Hyun Bin knew
all about it too, right?

299
00:17:27,120 --> 00:17:28,820
Director Yang is not like that.

300
00:17:28,990 --> 00:17:33,220
- What do you mean? He's like them.
- I'm telling you, he isn't!

301
00:17:33,290 --> 00:17:37,390
Don't tell me that. Mom was right.
If there's something they want,

302
00:17:37,460 --> 00:17:39,400
they will do whatever it takes.
That's how they are.

303
00:17:39,860 --> 00:17:40,860
Dad.

304
00:17:41,670 --> 00:17:44,770
- Are you going to tell Mom?
- Of course, I'm going to tell her.

305
00:17:45,200 --> 00:17:48,340
Am I supposed to watch our family
get played like this?

306
00:17:48,470 --> 00:17:51,880
What do you mean, "played?"
We used it as a chance to make up.

307
00:17:51,940 --> 00:17:53,310
Make up? Give me a break!

308
00:17:53,710 --> 00:17:56,380
I can't let this slide.
There's no way I'll let this slide!

309
00:17:56,850 --> 00:17:58,280
Dad.

310
00:17:59,150 --> 00:18:00,650
What? What's this?

311
00:18:02,850 --> 00:18:06,590
It's that jerk, Yang Dong Ik.
What scam is he trying to pull now?

312
00:18:06,990 --> 00:18:09,730
Gosh, take that, you jerk! Darn it.

313
00:18:11,860 --> 00:18:12,860
He's not answering?

314
00:18:14,330 --> 00:18:15,570
He's just rejecting my calls.

315
00:18:16,700 --> 00:18:20,270
Anything we say now will just sound
like an excuse, won't it?

316
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:24,010
I wish I could at least get a chance
to explain myself.

317
00:18:24,980 --> 00:18:28,710
But he won't even listen to me.
I feel like I'm going to explode.

318
00:18:31,180 --> 00:18:33,650
Honey, we can't just sit here
like this.

319
00:18:34,180 --> 00:18:36,490
I think we need to start preparing.

320
00:18:37,690 --> 00:18:41,290
The "Human Theater" shoot is soon.
If we don't do something now...

321
00:18:41,530 --> 00:18:42,690
Don't you do anything.

322
00:18:43,860 --> 00:18:45,000
I'll handle everything.

323
00:18:45,460 --> 00:18:47,000
What? How can I just do nothing?

324
00:18:47,560 --> 00:18:50,330
It's only a matter of time
before Dr. Han Seong Mi finds out.

325
00:18:52,370 --> 00:18:53,370
I suppose so.

326
00:18:55,870 --> 00:18:58,040
So, I hear you have that photo shoot
this weekend.

327
00:18:58,710 --> 00:19:00,010
Have you been practicing your poses?

328
00:19:00,610 --> 00:19:04,280
No, I haven't. What should I do?
I'm really worried.

329
00:19:05,250 --> 00:19:08,320
- Want to practice with me?
- With you?

330
00:19:09,220 --> 00:19:10,850
- I'm home.
- Welcome back.

331
00:19:10,920 --> 00:19:12,860
- You're back?
- Wait, you two came in together?

332
00:19:12,990 --> 00:19:15,490
- We ran into each other outside.
- Yes.

333
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:19,600
Mom...

334
00:19:20,030 --> 00:19:21,430
Dad.

335
00:19:22,770 --> 00:19:24,430
What is it?
Do you have something to say?

336
00:19:25,270 --> 00:19:26,270
No...

337
00:19:26,900 --> 00:19:29,010
No, it's nothing.
I'm going to go lie down.

338
00:19:31,710 --> 00:19:33,940
What was that?
What's wrong with your dad?

339
00:19:34,410 --> 00:19:36,950
I don't know either.
I'm going to head up.

340
00:19:41,290 --> 00:19:42,290
What's gotten into him?

341
00:19:49,230 --> 00:19:54,460
<i>- Let's all hold hands</i>
<i>- Let's all hold hands</i>

342
00:19:54,770 --> 00:19:57,470
<i>- Let our house</i>
<i>- Let our house</i>

343
00:19:57,530 --> 00:20:00,240
<i>- Be filled with laughter</i>
<i>- Be filled with laughter</i>

344
00:20:00,500 --> 00:20:02,740
<i>- Today, we become</i>
<i></i>- Dig in, please.

345
00:20:02,810 --> 00:20:05,910
<i>- A family again</i>
- You, too.

346
00:20:06,180 --> 00:20:08,780
<i>- From now on</i>
<i>- From now on</i>

347
00:20:08,780 --> 00:20:14,220
<i>- Let's live our lives with love</i>
<i>- Let's live our lives with love</i>

348
00:20:25,500 --> 00:20:28,170
What's wrong? You look upset.

349
00:20:30,370 --> 00:20:33,240
Something really hit me today.

350
00:20:33,870 --> 00:20:34,870
What?

351
00:20:35,440 --> 00:20:38,910
That you haven't been wrong
about a single thing.

352
00:20:40,040 --> 00:20:41,510
You're just figuring that out now?

353
00:20:41,850 --> 00:20:42,850
Yes.

354
00:20:43,850 --> 00:20:45,520
I've learned it the hard way.

355
00:20:46,650 --> 00:20:49,090
Did something happen to you?

356
00:20:52,220 --> 00:20:53,860
No, it's nothing.

357
00:20:54,830 --> 00:20:55,990
Nothing happened.

358
00:21:04,170 --> 00:21:08,370
<i>Today, we become a family again</i>

359
00:21:08,770 --> 00:21:13,480
<i>A precious day, though long overdue</i>

360
00:21:35,970 --> 00:21:39,440
Why haven't I heard from her?
Should I give her a call?

361
00:21:41,610 --> 00:21:42,610
What?

362
00:21:44,310 --> 00:21:45,340
You're home?

363
00:21:45,980 --> 00:21:47,010
Yes.

364
00:21:47,610 --> 00:21:48,910
How's your father doing?

365
00:21:49,980 --> 00:21:51,850
He took it really hard.

366
00:21:54,450 --> 00:21:56,450
I should have been there with you.

367
00:21:56,920 --> 00:21:58,720
I'm sorry I made you
go through that alone.

368
00:21:59,560 --> 00:22:03,230
No, it's okay.
It'd have been worse with you there.

369
00:22:04,560 --> 00:22:05,600
I suppose.

370
00:22:05,830 --> 00:22:09,570
It would be selfish of me to see him
just to make myself feel better.

371
00:22:11,370 --> 00:22:13,140
When the time is right,

372
00:22:13,540 --> 00:22:15,270
I'll be sure to give him
a proper apology.

373
00:22:17,010 --> 00:22:19,680
We've decided not to tell
the rest of the family.

374
00:22:20,580 --> 00:22:21,580
Really?

375
00:22:22,280 --> 00:22:25,320
Yes. Please tell your father that.

376
00:22:26,180 --> 00:22:27,220
I will.

377
00:22:28,220 --> 00:22:31,190
Okay, get some sleep.
I'll see you tomorrow.

378
00:22:53,610 --> 00:22:54,680
Is that Jeong Han?

379
00:22:56,180 --> 00:22:57,210
It's Hyun Bin.

380
00:22:59,650 --> 00:23:00,720
Hey.

381
00:23:01,490 --> 00:23:02,520
Really?

382
00:23:04,150 --> 00:23:06,020
Okay, and?

383
00:23:07,290 --> 00:23:08,290
I see.

384
00:23:08,790 --> 00:23:09,790
Got it.

385
00:23:12,730 --> 00:23:13,730
What did he say?

386
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:17,470
He said Jeong Han hasn't told
the rest of the family.

387
00:23:18,640 --> 00:23:20,100
That's such a relief.

388
00:23:20,400 --> 00:23:23,740
Then he'll still be on that show,
right?

389
00:23:24,570 --> 00:23:26,310
That's wonderful, honey.

390
00:23:29,950 --> 00:23:32,720
Aren't you happy?

391
00:23:33,420 --> 00:23:35,920
It's not like that means
he's forgiven me.

392
00:23:49,870 --> 00:23:53,170
- Are you done checking the script?
- Yes.

393
00:23:53,940 --> 00:23:55,110
Wait, what's wrong?

394
00:23:56,040 --> 00:23:57,040
Are you in pain?

395
00:23:57,340 --> 00:24:00,180
Yes, it's this constant,
squeezing pain.

396
00:24:00,710 --> 00:24:02,210
I think it's a stomach cramp.

397
00:24:04,180 --> 00:24:06,120
Hold on. I'll get you
some medicine, okay?

398
00:24:06,120 --> 00:24:07,150
Okay.

399
00:24:14,690 --> 00:24:16,860
Thanks for agreeing to meet,
Jeong Han.

400
00:24:17,490 --> 00:24:18,500
I...

401
00:24:19,330 --> 00:24:21,430
I'm pulling out of the show.

402
00:24:22,170 --> 00:24:23,170
I see.

403
00:24:23,630 --> 00:24:27,100
With how you feel, how can you act
like we're friends on camera?

404
00:24:27,270 --> 00:24:28,470
And another thing.

405
00:24:28,770 --> 00:24:31,640
You'll lose your VP title
at the Merchants' Association.

406
00:24:32,240 --> 00:24:33,240
What?

407
00:24:33,340 --> 00:24:37,750
I'll tell everyone at the market
that you staged the whole thing.

408
00:24:38,820 --> 00:24:39,850
Wait, Jeong Han.

409
00:24:40,250 --> 00:24:44,390
You know I need my position
to get the nomination, right?

410
00:24:45,820 --> 00:24:48,090
You should've thought of
the consequences.

411
00:24:49,890 --> 00:24:52,100
Jeong Han. Please, Jeong Han,
I'm begging you.

412
00:24:52,160 --> 00:24:56,230
- Jeong Han, please.
- Let go! It's not just the seat.

413
00:24:56,330 --> 00:24:58,300
Your clinic is done for too,
you jerk!

414
00:24:59,740 --> 00:25:01,440
- No, please!
- Let go!

415
00:25:01,440 --> 00:25:03,440
- Jeong Han, no! Please, spare me!
- Hey!

416
00:25:03,540 --> 00:25:05,110
- I said, let go!
- Jeong Han!

417
00:25:05,310 --> 00:25:06,410
Jeong Han...

418
00:25:07,240 --> 00:25:08,350
Jeong Han, don't go...

419
00:25:11,980 --> 00:25:14,320
Honey?

420
00:25:15,020 --> 00:25:16,590
Jeong Han, no!

421
00:25:18,020 --> 00:25:19,160
Honey!

422
00:25:22,690 --> 00:25:24,790
Honey, are you okay?

423
00:25:27,560 --> 00:25:28,970
Honey.

424
00:25:30,270 --> 00:25:31,370
I'm not okay.

425
00:25:41,580 --> 00:25:42,580
Mom.

426
00:25:42,850 --> 00:25:45,350
About my tutoring,
do you think Min Seo could do it?

427
00:25:45,580 --> 00:25:48,520
She was a great teacher helping me
with my English homework.

428
00:25:48,790 --> 00:25:52,760
My gosh, why didn't I think of that?
I'll have to ask her.

429
00:25:53,220 --> 00:25:56,660
And Mom, you should take Mr. Gong
from the clinic out for a meal.

430
00:25:57,090 --> 00:26:01,230
- What? Why?
- Why? He saved you from that scam.

431
00:26:02,970 --> 00:26:04,940
Right. He did.

432
00:26:05,170 --> 00:26:08,770
But it'd be weird to have a meal
with just the two of us, you know?

433
00:26:09,140 --> 00:26:11,040
- Mom.
- Yes?

434
00:26:11,110 --> 00:26:15,480
Forget what I said about
dating anyone but Mr. Gong.

435
00:26:15,750 --> 00:26:17,580
Our families are on good terms.

436
00:26:17,680 --> 00:26:20,220
So, as long as you like him,
why not?

437
00:26:31,900 --> 00:26:32,900
Right.

438
00:26:33,860 --> 00:26:36,930
Our families have made up.
There are no more obstacles.

439
00:26:37,430 --> 00:26:40,170
I shouldn't drag my feet.
I'm just going to go for it.

440
00:26:42,140 --> 00:26:44,610
- Right now!
- Gosh, Uncle.

441
00:26:45,010 --> 00:26:46,380
Didn't you throw that in the trash?

442
00:26:46,440 --> 00:26:50,350
Hey! Why would I throw this out?
Don't use this shampoo, okay?

443
00:26:50,850 --> 00:26:52,750
Did you come up here this early
just to talk about that?

444
00:26:52,820 --> 00:26:55,050
No, that's not it. Come here.

445
00:26:56,050 --> 00:26:58,220
- I need to talk to you.
- About what?

446
00:26:58,790 --> 00:27:01,120
- Attention!
- Attention.

447
00:27:01,120 --> 00:27:02,360
- Gong Woo Jae.
- Yes, sir.

448
00:27:02,460 --> 00:27:05,230
Recite for me how I, your uncle,
have raised you all this time.

449
00:27:06,760 --> 00:27:09,370
You fed me, housed me,
played with me, and clothed me.

450
00:27:09,430 --> 00:27:12,970
Exactly! Consider this
your chance to repay me.

451
00:27:13,040 --> 00:27:14,570
You have a new boss now, you know?

452
00:27:14,570 --> 00:27:16,210
- Be good to your new boss.
- What?

453
00:27:17,070 --> 00:27:19,240
No talking back.
This conversation is over.

454
00:27:19,440 --> 00:27:21,680
- The end. Now, attention!
- Goodness.

455
00:27:22,210 --> 00:27:23,210
What?

456
00:27:24,410 --> 00:27:25,520
What was that?

457
00:27:28,790 --> 00:27:29,850
Seong Mi.

458
00:27:31,490 --> 00:27:33,590
Is Jeong Han still not feeling well?

459
00:27:34,190 --> 00:27:36,430
It looks like he'll have to cancel
his appointments for the day.

460
00:27:37,060 --> 00:27:39,100
I'll keep an eye on him,
so you should get to work.

461
00:27:39,200 --> 00:27:41,300
- Okay. I'm running late. Let's go.
- Right.

462
00:27:41,300 --> 00:27:43,100
- Mother, we're heading out.
- You go on ahead.

463
00:27:43,100 --> 00:27:45,000
- I'm leaving now.
- Have a good day.

464
00:27:56,680 --> 00:27:58,210
Hey. How are you feeling?

465
00:27:59,120 --> 00:28:02,320
Hey, I think
it might be acute gastritis.

466
00:28:02,650 --> 00:28:04,790
I was even having stomach spasms
early this morning.

467
00:28:05,990 --> 00:28:07,120
Should you cancel
your appointments today?

468
00:28:08,320 --> 00:28:12,660
I can't. I have patients coming
from far away this afternoon.

469
00:28:14,230 --> 00:28:16,730
Okay, I'll postpone
your morning appointments.

470
00:28:16,730 --> 00:28:18,000
You rest up and come in later.

471
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:21,070
Okay. This is killing me.

472
00:28:22,010 --> 00:28:24,070
Haven't you been hanging out
with Bucket too much lately?

473
00:28:25,140 --> 00:28:27,080
- Lie down.
- All right.

474
00:28:35,450 --> 00:28:37,320
- Hey, Dong Ik.
- Hey, hi.

475
00:28:37,820 --> 00:28:39,690
- Good morning.
- You're out early.

476
00:28:41,760 --> 00:28:46,030
- I don't see Dr. Gong.
- He's not feeling well today.

477
00:28:46,100 --> 00:28:48,030
He's decided
to take the morning off.

478
00:28:48,230 --> 00:28:50,100
Oh, dear, what's wrong with him?

479
00:28:50,230 --> 00:28:51,900
It seems to be
stress-induced gastritis.

480
00:28:52,370 --> 00:28:55,840
- Please don't worry too much.
- I'll be heading in then.

481
00:28:56,370 --> 00:28:57,370
Have a good day.

482
00:28:59,280 --> 00:29:00,280
Dae Han.

483
00:29:00,840 --> 00:29:04,080
- Is Jeong Han really that sick?
- Yes.

484
00:29:05,050 --> 00:29:07,880
Hey, why the long face?
Is something wrong?

485
00:29:11,120 --> 00:29:12,320
What is it?

486
00:29:12,760 --> 00:29:15,190
Come on, you can tell me.
I'm all ears.

487
00:29:15,360 --> 00:29:16,790
We're practically family, aren't we?

488
00:29:17,360 --> 00:29:18,760
We are, right?

489
00:29:19,400 --> 00:29:21,330
Come on, tell me. What's going on?

490
00:29:25,840 --> 00:29:28,040
- No, it's nothing. Forget it.
- Hey, come on!

491
00:29:28,540 --> 00:29:30,110
Seriously, what is it? Tell me.

492
00:29:33,910 --> 00:29:35,350
I said, tell me! What...

493
00:29:35,910 --> 00:29:37,210
What is it? What's wrong?

494
00:29:40,780 --> 00:29:44,950
Why is kids' English so difficult?
Seriously!

495
00:29:45,220 --> 00:29:46,220
Yang Eun Bin.

496
00:29:46,560 --> 00:29:47,960
What? Don't bother me.

497
00:29:47,960 --> 00:29:49,990
I'm studying for this tutoring gig.
This is so not me.

498
00:29:50,330 --> 00:29:51,590
Then stop! You don't have to study.

499
00:29:51,590 --> 00:29:53,760
Ji Hu asked
if Min Seo could take over.

500
00:29:53,860 --> 00:29:57,100
Why? You can't just suddenly
decide that without talking to me.

501
00:29:57,170 --> 00:29:59,240
I need to start making money fast!

502
00:29:59,270 --> 00:30:03,110
Hey, use your brain.
Let Min Seo do the tutoring,

503
00:30:03,270 --> 00:30:05,480
and you can come work part-time
at the restaurant.

504
00:30:06,440 --> 00:30:07,510
You're a genius.

505
00:30:07,740 --> 00:30:11,450
But on one condition. Don't tell
your mom about this. Okay?

506
00:30:11,550 --> 00:30:14,880
Okay. Yes! I'm free!

507
00:30:14,950 --> 00:30:16,790
I'm free.

508
00:30:18,450 --> 00:30:22,090
It would be great
if she agrees to tutor him.

509
00:30:22,590 --> 00:30:26,960
But we need to verify her identity,
so get a copy of her visa.

510
00:30:28,930 --> 00:30:30,530
Okay. I'm hanging up now.

511
00:30:30,670 --> 00:30:32,600
(3H Acupressure Bed)

512
00:30:34,070 --> 00:30:35,740
Here's the operation manual
for the center.

513
00:30:40,410 --> 00:30:42,280
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

514
00:30:42,350 --> 00:30:44,480
Check freshness.

515
00:30:45,180 --> 00:30:47,550
You just need to check
the fridge temperature twice a day.

516
00:30:47,620 --> 00:30:48,820
Okay.

517
00:30:49,220 --> 00:30:51,750
I'll check the side dishes too,
just like you showed me.

518
00:30:51,750 --> 00:30:54,790
Okay. Now, pretend
a customer just walked in.

519
00:30:54,860 --> 00:30:56,330
Why don't you try greeting them?

520
00:30:59,830 --> 00:31:01,100
Welcome.

521
00:31:03,730 --> 00:31:06,570
Maybe try it
with a slightly higher tone.

522
00:31:08,970 --> 00:31:10,240
Welcome!

523
00:31:10,240 --> 00:31:11,310
(Franchise Trainee)

524
00:31:11,310 --> 00:31:13,410
With a little more confidence.

525
00:31:16,080 --> 00:31:17,450
Welcome!

526
00:31:17,610 --> 00:31:21,650
That's the tone to remember.
Next, show them to their seats,

527
00:31:21,720 --> 00:31:24,450
and then explain
how to use the kiosk.

528
00:31:24,820 --> 00:31:28,360
The kiosk...
Gosh, I'm so bad at this stuff.

529
00:31:29,060 --> 00:31:30,090
Here, let me show you.

530
00:31:30,630 --> 00:31:34,460
You just touch the screen,
then tap "Menu,"

531
00:31:34,530 --> 00:31:37,570
go to your cart, and hit "order."
That's it.

532
00:31:37,730 --> 00:31:41,140
- Simple, right?
- That's easier than I thought.

533
00:31:42,570 --> 00:31:46,580
Your system is great for beginners.
I think I can do this.

534
00:31:48,310 --> 00:31:49,910
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

535
00:31:49,980 --> 00:31:52,980
- Excuse me, Min Seo.
- Yes?

536
00:31:53,320 --> 00:31:56,690
By any chance, would you be willing
to tutor my son, Ji Hu?

537
00:31:57,650 --> 00:31:58,660
Me?

538
00:31:58,820 --> 00:32:01,890
The pay is much better than this.
What do you say?

539
00:32:02,660 --> 00:32:04,690
My Ji Hu is really set on it.

540
00:32:05,730 --> 00:32:07,600
I'm so sorry.

541
00:32:07,960 --> 00:32:11,600
I want to keep my restaurant job,
meet different kinds of people,

542
00:32:11,700 --> 00:32:13,770
and gain a lot of experience.

543
00:32:15,410 --> 00:32:17,140
Right, I can see that.

544
00:32:17,940 --> 00:32:21,240
- I was being selfish, wasn't I?
- Not at all.

545
00:32:24,310 --> 00:32:25,450
My gosh, sorry.

546
00:32:31,790 --> 00:32:36,560
- What are you doing?
- What? It's just a familiar scent.

547
00:32:43,030 --> 00:32:44,030
Dong Suk.

548
00:32:47,770 --> 00:32:49,470
Congratulations. You're a boss now.

549
00:32:49,470 --> 00:32:50,540
Thanks.

550
00:32:50,740 --> 00:32:51,870
Wait, hold on.

551
00:32:59,620 --> 00:33:00,650
Here!

552
00:33:01,020 --> 00:33:04,020
Oh, my. You really shouldn't have.

553
00:33:04,290 --> 00:33:05,920
I wanted to be the first one
to congratulate you.

554
00:33:06,860 --> 00:33:10,590
Honestly, it's all thanks to you.
I really mean it. Thank you.

555
00:33:12,760 --> 00:33:14,330
Hearing you say that...

556
00:33:14,630 --> 00:33:17,930
makes me feel so worthwhile.
I'm truly proud.

557
00:33:18,330 --> 00:33:19,600
So really, I should be thanking you.

558
00:33:20,070 --> 00:33:24,510
But did you really think
I had a boyfriend?

559
00:33:24,770 --> 00:33:29,050
Yes, of course!
You're so beautiful and kind,

560
00:33:29,210 --> 00:33:32,420
I couldn't imagine all the guys
in the world just leaving you alone.

561
00:33:32,850 --> 00:33:33,950
That's ridiculous.

562
00:33:34,550 --> 00:33:37,450
- You're the only one who thinks so.
- You think so?

563
00:33:37,920 --> 00:33:40,190
Are all the other guys
in the world fools, then?

564
00:33:42,090 --> 00:33:43,930
You're the only fool around here.

565
00:33:44,230 --> 00:33:47,700
Fine, I'm a fool.
A fool who only has eyes for you.

566
00:33:49,500 --> 00:33:50,770
Stop it.

567
00:33:53,900 --> 00:33:56,640
No, but really.
Wow, when you smile...

568
00:33:57,040 --> 00:33:59,510
It's just... Aren't you gorgeous?
You're so beautiful, seriously.

569
00:34:00,640 --> 00:34:03,310
You're like a fresh head of lettuce.

570
00:34:04,950 --> 00:34:06,980
- Lettuce?
- Yes, lettuce.

571
00:34:07,480 --> 00:34:08,720
Lettuce is my favorite.

572
00:34:11,590 --> 00:34:13,690
You're such a dork.

573
00:34:15,360 --> 00:34:16,930
I don't mind being a dork...

574
00:34:17,360 --> 00:34:19,160
as long as
I can make you smile every day.

575
00:34:25,900 --> 00:34:26,900
Let's go out.

576
00:34:28,570 --> 00:34:30,610
Let's try a real relationship,
Dong Suk.

577
00:34:34,040 --> 00:34:35,240
Could you...

578
00:34:36,050 --> 00:34:38,710
give me some time to think about it?

579
00:34:41,280 --> 00:34:42,290
Yes. Of course.

580
00:34:43,420 --> 00:34:44,420
All right.

581
00:34:45,290 --> 00:34:46,290
Thank you.

582
00:34:48,660 --> 00:34:49,860
So, ten minutes?

583
00:34:50,560 --> 00:34:53,360
- What?
- Just kidding.

584
00:34:53,930 --> 00:34:54,930
Thirty minutes?

585
00:34:56,200 --> 00:34:57,770
Give me a few days.

586
00:34:57,830 --> 00:35:01,170
Days? How can I wait that long?
What's there to think about?

587
00:35:02,570 --> 00:35:05,880
Dong Suk, we have little time
for love as it is.

588
00:35:06,510 --> 00:35:08,210
Our families have made up.

589
00:35:08,810 --> 00:35:10,910
There's nothing stopping us now.

590
00:35:13,950 --> 00:35:15,050
Wow, perfect timing.

591
00:35:16,320 --> 00:35:18,890
- Why?
- What perfect timing! Look.

592
00:35:19,190 --> 00:35:20,320
(Yang Dong Ik)

593
00:35:20,390 --> 00:35:21,860
Yang Dong Ik? You mean my brother?

594
00:35:23,160 --> 00:35:28,130
He's like a real brother to me now.
We're practically family already.

595
00:35:30,730 --> 00:35:31,730
Hey.

596
00:35:34,570 --> 00:35:36,210
Are you out of your mind? Seriously?

597
00:35:36,570 --> 00:35:38,070
What do you mean
you staged the whole thing?

598
00:35:38,940 --> 00:35:40,810
Man, why would you do that?

599
00:35:41,010 --> 00:35:42,010
(Korean Medicine Doctor
Yang Dong Ik)

600
00:35:42,010 --> 00:35:43,010
I'm sorry.

601
00:35:43,910 --> 00:35:45,180
I really have no excuse.

602
00:35:45,480 --> 00:35:48,420
Of course, you don't.
There's nothing you could say.

603
00:35:50,720 --> 00:35:51,720
Hey.

604
00:35:52,150 --> 00:35:54,820
Don't tell me...
When you got stabbed for my brother,

605
00:35:55,830 --> 00:35:58,290
- was that staged too?
- Hey, how could you even ask that?

606
00:35:58,630 --> 00:36:00,660
Come on, I'm not that low.

607
00:36:01,100 --> 00:36:02,730
How could I possibly stage
something like that?

608
00:36:03,200 --> 00:36:04,300
How should I know?

609
00:36:05,030 --> 00:36:07,000
Man, now I'm starting
to doubt everything.

610
00:36:08,540 --> 00:36:09,540
So?

611
00:36:10,210 --> 00:36:11,640
Are you going to help me or not?

612
00:36:12,580 --> 00:36:17,280
Gosh, this is driving me crazy.
Your wife is unbelievable. Truly.

613
00:36:17,480 --> 00:36:20,950
How could she suggest posting a clip
of her falling all over the place?

614
00:36:21,050 --> 00:36:23,320
Hey! You can insult me all you want,

615
00:36:23,820 --> 00:36:25,220
but don't you dare insult my wife.

616
00:36:26,220 --> 00:36:28,160
She was only doing it
because she was thinking of me.

617
00:36:28,520 --> 00:36:30,860
Man, you people are something else.
On so many levels.

618
00:36:31,430 --> 00:36:33,000
Gosh, this is driving me nuts!

619
00:36:38,100 --> 00:36:41,840
I've drafted the interview
Q and A guide for the shoot.

620
00:36:41,900 --> 00:36:43,340
Could you take a look, Director?

621
00:36:44,610 --> 00:36:46,210
Good work, Ms. Gong.

622
00:36:51,110 --> 00:36:52,110
Yes.

623
00:36:53,750 --> 00:36:55,320
I'm sorry, who?

624
00:36:56,590 --> 00:36:58,190
Director Yang's mother?

625
00:37:00,360 --> 00:37:01,820
Yes. Hello.

626
00:37:03,030 --> 00:37:04,760
Okay, I understand.

627
00:37:06,830 --> 00:37:08,800
Wait, my stepmother? What about her?

628
00:37:09,000 --> 00:37:12,840
She said she was nearby on an errand
and wants to meet.

629
00:37:14,940 --> 00:37:16,940
Gosh, my father, seriously.

630
00:37:17,040 --> 00:37:19,840
I told him to deal with it himself,
but he sent my stepmother instead.

631
00:37:20,710 --> 00:37:21,710
I'll go see her.

632
00:37:22,350 --> 00:37:23,350
I'll go with you.

633
00:37:23,480 --> 00:37:26,020
No, it's okay.
She doesn't know about us.

634
00:37:29,050 --> 00:37:31,790
Don't worry.
She probably just came to apologize.

635
00:37:32,050 --> 00:37:34,720
I'm sure. It must have been weighing
on her mind.

636
00:37:35,860 --> 00:37:38,860
Since we decided to drop it
without telling our families,

637
00:37:39,230 --> 00:37:42,400
I'll go tell her
that she can rest easy now.

638
00:37:47,570 --> 00:37:48,770
To be honest,

639
00:37:51,210 --> 00:37:52,580
I have no intention of apologizing.

640
00:37:54,910 --> 00:37:56,910
It's time you were honest too,
Gong Ju Ah.

641
00:37:57,380 --> 00:37:59,180
During the One-Point Lesson event,

642
00:37:59,450 --> 00:38:01,050
you pushed me on purpose,
didn't you?

643
00:38:02,220 --> 00:38:03,950
- Excuse me?
- That day...

644
00:38:04,720 --> 00:38:07,890
Poking me with that pin,
and then pushing me...

645
00:38:08,290 --> 00:38:10,390
It was all deliberate, wasn't it?

646
00:38:11,990 --> 00:38:13,700
If that's what you thought,

647
00:38:13,900 --> 00:38:17,530
then why did you defend me
at the disciplinary hearing?

648
00:38:18,770 --> 00:38:20,900
The reason
I posted that video of myself...

649
00:38:21,370 --> 00:38:23,510
was to put pressure on Dr. Gong.

650
00:38:23,610 --> 00:38:27,310
I never had any intention
of hurting you, Ju Ah.

651
00:38:30,780 --> 00:38:33,720
I don't regret posting that video.

652
00:38:34,520 --> 00:38:37,350
Honestly, the company benefited
from my video,

653
00:38:37,350 --> 00:38:38,550
and our families made up,

654
00:38:39,460 --> 00:38:42,060
so in the end,
didn't it all work out for the best?

655
00:38:45,030 --> 00:38:48,960
Then why did you ask to see me?

656
00:38:51,300 --> 00:38:55,500
I can't help that you
and Dr. Gong found out, but...

657
00:38:56,740 --> 00:38:59,240
please try to keep it
from the rest of the family.

658
00:38:59,880 --> 00:39:01,080
If they find out now,

659
00:39:01,340 --> 00:39:02,810
it would just be a huge shock,
wouldn't it?

660
00:39:05,750 --> 00:39:06,750
And...

661
00:39:07,520 --> 00:39:08,650
about this whole thing...

662
00:39:09,490 --> 00:39:13,160
We can't have this making things
awkward for Hyun Bin, right?

663
00:39:15,220 --> 00:39:19,060
Besides, who would believe rumors
from a mere employee anyway?

664
00:39:19,830 --> 00:39:22,470
Anyway, just don't spread rumors
at work.

665
00:39:23,200 --> 00:39:24,200
Especially...

666
00:39:25,840 --> 00:39:27,000
to the VP.

667
00:39:27,800 --> 00:39:28,800
Got it?

668
00:39:48,060 --> 00:39:49,490
Did she give you a sincere apology?

669
00:39:50,230 --> 00:39:51,630
She said she has
no intention of apologizing.

670
00:39:52,130 --> 00:39:54,830
What? No way. That can't be right.

671
00:39:55,200 --> 00:39:57,430
What, are you saying I'm lying?

672
00:39:58,230 --> 00:40:01,470
No, I'm not saying you're lying.

673
00:40:02,070 --> 00:40:04,570
- I thought you misunderstood.
- Misunderstood?

674
00:40:04,770 --> 00:40:06,210
Should we check
the security footage together?

675
00:40:07,610 --> 00:40:10,610
What? Since you trust
your stepmother more than me,

676
00:40:10,680 --> 00:40:12,250
you need to see some proof, right?

677
00:40:12,620 --> 00:40:13,650
Babe.

678
00:40:15,680 --> 00:40:17,150
Why did you lie to me?

679
00:40:17,790 --> 00:40:18,790
Me?

680
00:40:18,990 --> 00:40:22,660
She thinks I pricked her
and pushed her during the lesson...

681
00:40:23,060 --> 00:40:24,960
on purpose.

682
00:40:25,960 --> 00:40:27,800
But you told me
that wasn't the case at all.

683
00:40:28,830 --> 00:40:29,870
That's...

684
00:40:31,330 --> 00:40:32,870
So you were lying.

685
00:40:33,700 --> 00:40:34,800
Wow. Unbelievable.

686
00:40:36,540 --> 00:40:39,010
- Look, babe.
- No, I'm done talking.

687
00:40:39,540 --> 00:40:41,710
We should end this
before it's too late.

688
00:40:43,050 --> 00:40:44,550
Wait, we aren't done.

689
00:40:44,550 --> 00:40:45,920
- Where are you going?
- Let go of me!

690
00:40:47,220 --> 00:40:49,850
Right now,
getting back together with you...

691
00:40:50,150 --> 00:40:51,950
I regret it so much I could scream.

692
00:40:57,330 --> 00:40:58,330
Would it...

693
00:40:59,600 --> 00:41:02,730
have been better
if I had never come back to Korea?

694
00:41:03,730 --> 00:41:07,240
It was never going to work out
between us anyway.

695
00:41:08,700 --> 00:41:12,410
Your stepmother will only accept
the VP as her daughter-in-law.

696
00:41:13,240 --> 00:41:15,380
That's not true.
I already told her...

697
00:41:15,380 --> 00:41:17,880
Get the talisman under your bed,
and then we'll talk.

698
00:41:18,610 --> 00:41:21,820
Your mother put it there
with her earnest hopes, after all.

699
00:42:07,300 --> 00:42:09,230
Se Ri. How was your session?

700
00:42:09,600 --> 00:42:13,270
It was fine.
Did you talk to that part-timer?

701
00:42:13,770 --> 00:42:15,770
Yes, but she said no.

702
00:42:16,640 --> 00:42:17,640
Really?

703
00:42:18,070 --> 00:42:21,280
She wanted real-world experience
instead of tutoring.

704
00:42:22,280 --> 00:42:25,150
So, what's with the porridge?
Are you feeling sick?

705
00:42:25,950 --> 00:42:28,380
It's for my husband.
He hasn't been eating.

706
00:42:29,490 --> 00:42:32,450
You get this worried just because
my brother skips a single meal?

707
00:42:32,520 --> 00:42:34,160
You look like
it's the end of the world.

708
00:42:35,790 --> 00:42:38,460
What is it?
Is something bothering you?

709
00:42:39,860 --> 00:42:40,860
No, it's nothing.

710
00:42:41,460 --> 00:42:44,730
What is it? Don't just suffer
in silence. Tell me.

711
00:42:49,270 --> 00:42:50,270
Okay, but...

712
00:42:50,940 --> 00:42:52,310
promise you won't panic.

713
00:42:53,840 --> 00:42:56,850
All right, I'll stay calm,

714
00:42:57,350 --> 00:42:58,680
so just tell me what's going on.

715
00:43:03,420 --> 00:43:05,650
You know
that video of Bucket's wife falling?

716
00:43:06,190 --> 00:43:07,190
Yes.

717
00:43:08,160 --> 00:43:09,220
That video...

718
00:43:10,390 --> 00:43:12,560
Bucket was the one who posted it.

719
00:43:14,230 --> 00:43:17,600
- What?
- You said you wouldn't panic.

720
00:43:17,670 --> 00:43:19,440
How could I be calm
after hearing that?

721
00:43:19,800 --> 00:43:22,240
Are you crazy?
How could you do a thing like that?

722
00:43:22,740 --> 00:43:24,370
Wow, you and my brother
are a real piece of work.

723
00:43:24,770 --> 00:43:28,080
Hey, it's not like we knew
it would get this out of hand.

724
00:43:28,240 --> 00:43:32,080
I swear, I can't deal with this.
So, what are we going to do now?

725
00:43:32,780 --> 00:43:33,880
Good question.

726
00:43:34,080 --> 00:43:35,880
It looks like
their friendship is over.

727
00:43:36,250 --> 00:43:38,920
What if Dr. Gong backs out
of "Human Theater?"

728
00:43:39,460 --> 00:43:42,860
- Is that all you're worried about?
- Well, what else is there?

729
00:43:42,930 --> 00:43:45,560
What? Gosh, I don't know. Whatever.

730
00:43:46,260 --> 00:43:48,600
Goodness, what am I going to do now?

731
00:43:57,340 --> 00:43:58,440
What do you think?

732
00:43:58,940 --> 00:44:00,110
You have to forgive him.

733
00:44:00,810 --> 00:44:02,440
Come on, you're the bigger person.

734
00:44:03,150 --> 00:44:04,150
Are you serious?

735
00:44:04,710 --> 00:44:05,710
Hey, don't tell me...

736
00:44:06,350 --> 00:44:07,850
Bucket got to you, didn't he?

737
00:44:08,120 --> 00:44:10,250
Come on. What do you take me for?

738
00:44:11,420 --> 00:44:13,520
Sure, his intentions weren't great,

739
00:44:13,860 --> 00:44:15,890
but things worked out
in the end, right?

740
00:44:16,760 --> 00:44:18,930
Are you taking
Bucket's side right now?

741
00:44:19,060 --> 00:44:22,160
I'm not taking his side.
Holding a grudge only hurts you.

742
00:44:26,540 --> 00:44:28,770
(Menu)

743
00:44:31,410 --> 00:44:33,440
The fact that I'm this hurt...

744
00:44:34,540 --> 00:44:36,450
must mean I was really happy
we made up.

745
00:44:37,710 --> 00:44:38,710
But I really...

746
00:44:39,350 --> 00:44:41,580
I thought Bucket
was being genuine with me.

747
00:44:42,550 --> 00:44:43,790
But...

748
00:44:44,450 --> 00:44:46,520
I don't know about anything else,

749
00:44:47,160 --> 00:44:50,930
but him taking that knife for you...
I think that was real.

750
00:44:51,390 --> 00:44:54,630
I thought about what I would've done
in his shoes.

751
00:44:55,200 --> 00:44:57,830
I couldn't have done it.
And neither could you.

752
00:45:00,040 --> 00:45:01,140
You're right.

753
00:45:02,570 --> 00:45:05,410
Seong Mi said the same thing,
that it was a protective instinct.

754
00:45:07,440 --> 00:45:08,740
You're not going to tell Seong Mi,
are you?

755
00:45:09,510 --> 00:45:13,420
You can't tell her. Not a word.
If she finds out, it's all over.

756
00:45:29,100 --> 00:45:32,730
I thought you were sick.
Why were you out drinking?

757
00:45:35,070 --> 00:45:37,910
What's going on?
You're hiding something, aren't you?

758
00:45:39,510 --> 00:45:40,510
Seong Mi.

759
00:45:41,810 --> 00:45:44,650
I can't back out of doing that show,
can I?

760
00:45:45,210 --> 00:45:46,680
Are you out of your mind?

761
00:45:47,050 --> 00:45:48,680
After we've already signed
the contract?

762
00:45:49,280 --> 00:45:50,520
Do you think
this contract is a joke?

763
00:45:53,490 --> 00:45:54,960
Why the sudden change of heart?

764
00:45:55,590 --> 00:45:57,060
Did you and Bucket get into a fight?

765
00:45:57,790 --> 00:45:59,860
No, that's not it.

766
00:46:00,630 --> 00:46:01,660
Then what is it?

767
00:46:03,130 --> 00:46:04,900
It feels like
you're hiding something again.

768
00:46:05,430 --> 00:46:08,240
No, I'm not. Okay?

769
00:46:08,740 --> 00:46:11,810
I'm really not hiding anything.
Seriously.

770
00:46:12,740 --> 00:46:14,240
I should wash up.

771
00:46:14,740 --> 00:46:16,350
- Give it here.
- Okay.

772
00:46:26,520 --> 00:46:30,160
He has some nerve.
He didn't even call. Unbelievable.

773
00:46:33,630 --> 00:46:35,000
Wait, we aren't done.

774
00:46:35,000 --> 00:46:36,630
- Where are you going?
- Let go of me!

775
00:46:37,730 --> 00:46:40,440
Right now,
getting back together with you...

776
00:46:40,700 --> 00:46:42,440
I regret it so much I could scream.

777
00:46:47,840 --> 00:46:48,840
Would it...

778
00:46:50,150 --> 00:46:53,220
have been better
if I had never come back to Korea?

779
00:46:54,720 --> 00:46:58,190
Gosh, why did he have to say that?

780
00:46:59,390 --> 00:47:00,390
Oh, boy.

781
00:47:02,620 --> 00:47:04,990
Gosh, I don't know.
I'm the one who should be mad here.

782
00:47:23,410 --> 00:47:25,710
(148 Suyang-ro)

783
00:47:28,680 --> 00:47:30,320
- Uncle.
- Hey, come here.

784
00:47:31,620 --> 00:47:32,820
You know about it, right?

785
00:47:33,160 --> 00:47:37,290
- About what?
- That video. They set it up.

786
00:47:37,730 --> 00:47:38,960
Uncle, how did you find out?

787
00:47:39,330 --> 00:47:41,400
Gosh, Dad promised
he'd keep it a secret.

788
00:47:41,900 --> 00:47:45,430
Uncle, if Mom or Grandma finds out,
it'll be war between our families.

789
00:47:45,500 --> 00:47:47,300
That's exactly what I'm saying.

790
00:47:47,640 --> 00:47:48,970
Keep a tight lid on this,
you hear me?

791
00:47:49,400 --> 00:47:50,870
You're the one
who should watch your mouth, Uncle.

792
00:47:50,940 --> 00:47:53,880
Come on.
Anything I hear just disappears.

793
00:47:53,940 --> 00:47:56,010
It's never coming out
of my mouth. All right?

794
00:47:59,280 --> 00:48:02,220
- You...
- Gong Woo Jae, what did you catch?

795
00:48:03,090 --> 00:48:05,620
Shouldn't the question be,
"When did you start listening?"

796
00:48:05,650 --> 00:48:07,890
What? When did you start listening?

797
00:48:08,490 --> 00:48:11,390
The video of the fall.
They set it all up.

798
00:48:15,030 --> 00:48:16,030
Good grief...

799
00:48:24,870 --> 00:48:28,440
Goodness,
what's with the gloomy atmosphere?

800
00:48:29,110 --> 00:48:30,510
Is something wrong, everyone?

801
00:48:31,180 --> 00:48:32,710
No, it's nothing.

802
00:48:33,520 --> 00:48:35,650
Ji Hu, Min Seo said she's not
interested in the tutoring job.

803
00:48:36,020 --> 00:48:37,020
- Why not?
- Why not?

804
00:48:37,590 --> 00:48:40,660
I don't know. Why don't you try
talking her into it?

805
00:48:42,560 --> 00:48:43,560
You got this!

806
00:48:43,860 --> 00:48:44,860
Leave it to me.

807
00:48:45,260 --> 00:48:46,260
Oh, right.

808
00:48:46,500 --> 00:48:48,400
On the day
Dong Suk's restaurant opens,

809
00:48:48,830 --> 00:48:50,670
let's invite Dr. Gong
and his family.

810
00:48:51,630 --> 00:48:53,440
That's a fantastic idea!

811
00:48:53,700 --> 00:48:57,070
Father, don't you think
it's a bit too soon for that?

812
00:48:57,770 --> 00:49:00,980
I still haven't gotten
the hang of anything.

813
00:49:01,340 --> 00:49:04,810
Right, Father.
Isn't it a bit too soon?

814
00:49:05,180 --> 00:49:07,280
Still, it's the proper thing to do.

815
00:49:07,950 --> 00:49:10,450
They invited us over for a meal
and even cooked oxtail soup for us.

816
00:49:10,750 --> 00:49:13,220
It's only right that we invite them
and treat them in return.

817
00:49:14,020 --> 00:49:15,020
Father.

818
00:49:15,960 --> 00:49:18,790
- The thing is, Jeong Han and I...
- Honey.

819
00:49:21,600 --> 00:49:24,430
What? Why did you stop mid-sentence?

820
00:49:24,970 --> 00:49:27,800
Right! You were about to agree,
weren't you?

821
00:49:28,700 --> 00:49:32,370
Great! Let's invite them
to my grand opening, okay?

822
00:49:32,840 --> 00:49:35,840
Yes. I'll help too, Dong Suk.

823
00:49:36,580 --> 00:49:38,250
You're okay with this, right, honey?

824
00:49:52,460 --> 00:49:54,400
(Managing Director
Pacundo Ignacio de la Cruz Yang)

825
00:49:54,930 --> 00:49:57,830
He has no outside meetings,
so why isn't he at work?

826
00:49:58,370 --> 00:50:01,500
Don't tell me he's skipping work
just because we had a fight.

827
00:50:03,210 --> 00:50:04,210
Unbelievable.

828
00:50:08,110 --> 00:50:10,080
(Taehan Group)

829
00:50:10,950 --> 00:50:13,050
(Taehan Group)

830
00:50:13,320 --> 00:50:14,320
Vice President.

831
00:50:17,390 --> 00:50:19,350
If it's not an emergency,
don't come running in here.

832
00:50:19,590 --> 00:50:20,590
It is an emergency.

833
00:50:21,460 --> 00:50:24,130
The head of Cartio who tried
to recruit Director Yang,

834
00:50:24,230 --> 00:50:26,630
Berta Rubio, arrived
in Korea this morning.

835
00:50:27,530 --> 00:50:28,530
So?

836
00:50:28,930 --> 00:50:31,430
Director Yang
took the day off today.

837
00:50:32,070 --> 00:50:33,070
What?

838
00:50:42,010 --> 00:50:43,150
I knew it.

839
00:50:43,650 --> 00:50:44,680
Why? What is it?

840
00:50:44,980 --> 00:50:47,320
They're saying Director Yang
was recruited by Cartio.

841
00:50:47,620 --> 00:50:48,650
What?

842
00:50:50,250 --> 00:50:53,290
Apparently, he took the day off
to meet with their representative.

843
00:50:54,190 --> 00:50:56,760
If he leaves for Spain,
what are we going to do?

844
00:51:00,960 --> 00:51:05,400
Come on, please do it.
Please? I'm begging you.

845
00:51:05,900 --> 00:51:10,870
Believe me, I won't be any help.
I don't know Korean teaching styles.

846
00:51:11,570 --> 00:51:13,510
Then what if we throw in
a free place to stay?

847
00:51:13,780 --> 00:51:17,510
Come on, if you save on rent,
you'll save up money faster, right?

848
00:51:17,750 --> 00:51:20,520
I told you.
I don't like being in anyone's debt.

849
00:51:20,580 --> 00:51:24,890
Debt? No! It's a job perk!
You'd just teach a few hours a day,

850
00:51:24,950 --> 00:51:28,660
and spend the afternoons
traveling and sightseeing. Okay?

851
00:51:29,320 --> 00:51:31,260
She's right.
It sounds like a pretty good offer.

852
00:51:31,330 --> 00:51:32,330
You should think it over.

853
00:51:32,390 --> 00:51:34,200
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

854
00:51:40,370 --> 00:51:41,540
Look.

855
00:51:42,500 --> 00:51:45,640
I'm doing this because
I want to be with Woo Jae. Okay?

856
00:51:46,070 --> 00:51:49,210
It's hard to see him these days
because he's so busy with work.

857
00:51:53,950 --> 00:51:55,580
This is for you.

858
00:51:56,280 --> 00:51:58,420
I bought you a shirt.
I thought it would look good on you.

859
00:51:58,850 --> 00:51:59,860
My gosh.

860
00:52:02,320 --> 00:52:04,830
I'm not supposed to accept
things like this.

861
00:52:05,230 --> 00:52:08,660
What? It's just a little something
for saving my life.

862
00:52:08,760 --> 00:52:09,760
I wanted to thank you.

863
00:52:10,200 --> 00:52:11,570
Really, you don't have to.

864
00:52:14,770 --> 00:52:18,270
Then, are you free on Sunday?

865
00:52:19,040 --> 00:52:20,810
I'd like to treat you
to a nice meal.

866
00:52:21,340 --> 00:52:22,640
To thank you for saving me.

867
00:52:23,550 --> 00:52:27,080
I'm actually on duty this Sunday.

868
00:52:27,780 --> 00:52:28,820
I see.

869
00:52:31,090 --> 00:52:33,620
And really,
you don't have to repay me.

870
00:52:34,860 --> 00:52:38,190
I was just doing my job.

871
00:52:42,000 --> 00:52:44,330
Right. I understand.

872
00:52:45,300 --> 00:52:46,300
Okay.

873
00:52:52,170 --> 00:52:54,310
(Police)

874
00:52:54,310 --> 00:52:56,780
Hey, you're not on duty this Sunday,
you fool.

875
00:52:57,450 --> 00:53:01,350
Why would you turn her down?
I thought you liked Nurse Oh.

876
00:53:02,820 --> 00:53:03,890
I do like her.

877
00:53:05,320 --> 00:53:06,390
That's why I turned her down.

878
00:53:08,560 --> 00:53:09,560
What?

879
00:53:11,860 --> 00:53:14,000
(Civil Affairs Office,
Open 24 Hours)

880
00:53:14,000 --> 00:53:15,460
Oh, man...

881
00:53:16,870 --> 00:53:19,230
An invitation to Dong Suk's
grand opening?

882
00:53:19,700 --> 00:53:22,570
Yes. It'll be my treat,

883
00:53:22,870 --> 00:53:24,470
so I hope you'll all be there.

884
00:53:25,410 --> 00:53:29,380
Of course, we'll be there.
The whole family will be thrilled.

885
00:53:30,910 --> 00:53:35,150
Dong Suk's been doing well lately.
She even has a new boyfriend.

886
00:53:35,850 --> 00:53:38,320
Dae Han will meet someone special
soon too.

887
00:53:40,020 --> 00:53:41,290
I hear he already has.

888
00:53:42,190 --> 00:53:43,190
Oh, really?

889
00:53:43,930 --> 00:53:45,630
That's wonderful news.

890
00:53:46,800 --> 00:53:47,800
It is.

891
00:53:50,530 --> 00:53:52,530
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

892
00:53:54,200 --> 00:53:55,340
Oh, that's right.

893
00:53:56,710 --> 00:54:00,480
Yes, Councilor Hwang.
I'm sorry. I forgot to call first.

894
00:54:00,740 --> 00:54:03,010
I do apologize. Yes.

895
00:54:10,620 --> 00:54:11,820
Really?

896
00:54:12,620 --> 00:54:15,460
He postponed the meeting
with Councilor Hwang, not cancel it?

897
00:54:15,520 --> 00:54:18,330
Yes. I had to really get on
my brother's case yesterday.

898
00:54:18,530 --> 00:54:20,160
Do you have any idea
how hard I had to persuade him?

899
00:54:20,230 --> 00:54:22,860
Dong Ik, you'll be on
"Human Theater" thanks to me.

900
00:54:23,370 --> 00:54:24,830
Don't you forget it, you hear me?

901
00:54:25,800 --> 00:54:26,800
Dae Han.

902
00:54:27,700 --> 00:54:30,170
Honestly, I couldn't care less
about being on that show.

903
00:54:31,070 --> 00:54:32,110
What?

904
00:54:32,470 --> 00:54:34,640
As long as I can still be friends
with Jeong Han,

905
00:54:35,840 --> 00:54:38,380
I really don't need
any of that other stuff.

906
00:54:40,050 --> 00:54:41,480
He'll see how sincere you are.

907
00:54:42,180 --> 00:54:43,350
Don't worry about it.

908
00:54:44,620 --> 00:54:45,750
(Korean Medicine Doctor
Yang Dong Ik)

909
00:54:45,820 --> 00:54:47,790
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

910
00:54:49,020 --> 00:54:51,630
- Hey, it's Jeong Han.
- What?

911
00:54:52,330 --> 00:54:53,760
Hurry, answer it.

912
00:54:57,200 --> 00:54:59,200
Oh, hey, Jeong Han.

913
00:55:07,510 --> 00:55:09,040
Hey, are you just going to sit here
like this?

914
00:55:09,910 --> 00:55:11,380
Then what am I supposed to do?

915
00:55:12,050 --> 00:55:14,180
Just call him.

916
00:55:14,450 --> 00:55:16,320
You have to at least find out
what's going on.

917
00:55:16,620 --> 00:55:19,590
He won't even pick up for the VP.
You think he'll answer me?

918
00:55:19,820 --> 00:55:21,060
Then you keep calling
until he picks up.

919
00:55:21,390 --> 00:55:23,960
Would you be happy if he gets
recruited and moves to Spain?

920
00:55:24,130 --> 00:55:25,390
If he wants to go, then let him.

921
00:55:26,930 --> 00:55:30,970
Wow, that's harsh. Fine, I'll do it.

922
00:55:31,330 --> 00:55:32,430
- If he doesn't pick up,
- My gosh.

923
00:55:32,430 --> 00:55:35,170
I'll keep calling until he answers.
Darn it.

924
00:55:35,170 --> 00:55:36,940
(Director Yang)

925
00:55:37,440 --> 00:55:39,540
He's picking up. Hello?

926
00:55:40,010 --> 00:55:42,040
Director,
why weren't you picking up?

927
00:55:43,310 --> 00:55:45,080
What's wrong with your voice?

928
00:55:46,610 --> 00:55:48,080
Oh, no. Are you okay?

929
00:55:49,150 --> 00:55:52,390
A cold with body aches.
Oh, so you've been sick.

930
00:55:53,390 --> 00:55:54,490
Man...

931
00:56:03,060 --> 00:56:04,270
Are you okay?

932
00:56:05,130 --> 00:56:06,270
I heard you were sick.

933
00:56:09,600 --> 00:56:11,040
So why did you want to meet?

934
00:56:15,210 --> 00:56:18,850
- It's about "Human Theater."
- Look, if you're not comfortable,

935
00:56:19,210 --> 00:56:22,280
you don't have to be on the show.
And if you want,

936
00:56:22,650 --> 00:56:24,620
I'll step down as VP
of the Merchants' Association.

937
00:56:25,220 --> 00:56:28,420
I don't need executive experience
or a nomination.

938
00:56:29,520 --> 00:56:30,530
Do it all.

939
00:56:32,030 --> 00:56:33,060
Really?

940
00:56:34,030 --> 00:56:37,070
Yes. Do it all.
A promise is a promise.

941
00:56:39,000 --> 00:56:40,000
But...

942
00:56:41,340 --> 00:56:42,570
from now on,

943
00:56:44,040 --> 00:56:45,270
we're not friends.

944
00:56:46,240 --> 00:56:47,240
What?

945
00:57:08,200 --> 00:57:10,470
Hey. So?

946
00:57:10,600 --> 00:57:13,540
- Did you two work things out?
- What are you doing here?

947
00:57:13,840 --> 00:57:17,410
I was passing by and saw you go in.
You made up with Bucket, right?

948
00:57:17,540 --> 00:57:18,570
Made up?

949
00:57:18,940 --> 00:57:21,540
- I told him we're done. Darn it.
- What? Why?

950
00:57:21,940 --> 00:57:24,910
Then are you backing out
of "Human Theater?"

951
00:57:25,080 --> 00:57:27,850
I have no choice but to do the show.
We already signed a contract.

952
00:57:28,320 --> 00:57:29,720
But from now on, Bucket...

953
00:57:30,750 --> 00:57:32,690
I'm just going to treat him
like a business partner.

954
00:57:33,890 --> 00:57:34,890
Hey.

955
00:57:35,720 --> 00:57:36,720
Jeong Han!

956
00:57:41,860 --> 00:57:43,600
Of all people... Darn it.

957
00:57:45,870 --> 00:57:47,040
Man.

958
00:58:22,470 --> 00:58:25,140
(Medicine)

959
00:58:32,810 --> 00:58:34,720
He needs to eat something
before he can take his medicine.

960
00:58:35,820 --> 00:58:37,120
But I can't just wake him up.

961
00:58:49,460 --> 00:58:50,630
(Dress the heart. Swing for hope.)

962
00:58:57,340 --> 00:58:58,510
I haven't seen this in a while.

963
00:58:59,310 --> 00:59:01,010
I can't believe you still have this.

964
00:59:08,450 --> 00:59:10,220
(From Hyun Bin, To Ju Ah)

965
00:59:12,320 --> 00:59:15,090
Happy 18th birthday, Ju Ah.

966
00:59:15,690 --> 00:59:18,690
Today, I ate a dish called Milanesa.

967
00:59:19,260 --> 00:59:22,460
Eating this reminds me
of the pork cutlet place we went to.

968
00:59:24,570 --> 00:59:29,400
I went to see the Carnival parade
in Buenos Aires today.

969
00:59:30,040 --> 00:59:34,640
There's a cool dance called Murga.
I wish we could've seen it together.

970
00:59:36,610 --> 00:59:39,480
I was so sick today that I had to go
to the emergency room.

971
00:59:40,620 --> 00:59:42,250
I thought I was okay being alone,

972
00:59:42,680 --> 00:59:44,550
but being sick suddenly made me
feel so lonely.

973
00:59:45,990 --> 00:59:48,490
But I refuse to cry.

974
00:59:49,090 --> 00:59:50,290
I'm going to be happy,
no matter what.

975
00:59:51,690 --> 00:59:55,560
Because when we meet again someday,
I want you to say I've done well.

976
00:59:57,430 --> 00:59:58,430
And...

977
00:59:59,100 --> 01:00:00,670
if I ever see you again,

978
01:00:02,170 --> 01:00:03,940
I'll never let you go.

979
01:00:31,300 --> 01:00:32,300
Babe.

980
01:00:32,900 --> 01:00:33,970
Are you okay?

981
01:00:36,040 --> 01:00:37,870
What if I get you sick?

982
01:00:40,070 --> 01:00:41,140
I don't care.

983
01:01:05,970 --> 01:01:08,140
(Grandma)

984
01:01:15,010 --> 01:01:16,110
Hello?

985
01:01:16,980 --> 01:01:19,550
Ju Ah. Where are you?

986
01:01:22,850 --> 01:01:23,890
Grandma?

987
01:01:24,350 --> 01:01:25,420
Give me the phone.

988
01:01:26,190 --> 01:01:28,620
Hey, Gong Ju Ah!
Where are you right now?

989
01:01:31,430 --> 01:01:34,360
- Well...
- Hey, you...

990
01:01:34,630 --> 01:01:36,260
Did you just stay out all night
without saying a word?

991
01:01:36,800 --> 01:01:38,270
Hey, where are you right now?

992
01:01:39,670 --> 01:01:41,440
- Well...
- Babe.

993
01:01:44,340 --> 01:01:47,180
- What? "Babe?"
- What?

994
01:01:47,880 --> 01:01:50,680
Don't tell me you're with a man!

995
01:02:29,850 --> 01:02:32,720
(Recipe For Love)

996
01:02:32,790 --> 01:02:36,290
Dong Suk, you're the recipe for love
my life has always needed.

997
01:02:36,460 --> 01:02:40,560
Whatever we face, I won't let go.
We'll get through this.

998
01:02:41,660 --> 01:02:43,660
What if someone sees us?

999
01:02:44,070 --> 01:02:46,970
- What in the world?
- You know Ju Ah lives with us.

1000
01:02:46,970 --> 01:02:47,970
Mom!

1001
01:02:47,970 --> 01:02:50,510
She can't be out all night
without permission!

1002
01:02:50,910 --> 01:02:53,270
Let's take this chance to be honest
and get their blessing.

1003
